    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Review of Poecilimon species with inflated pronotum: description of four new taxa within an acoustically diverse group" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441749>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441777>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441781>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441789>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441791>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441793> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441749>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distribution of Poecilimon (P.) inflatus group: A—Total range, B—P. inflatus inflatus, P. inflatus lyciae, P. martinae martinae, P. martinae tlos and P. cretensis, C—P. antalyaensis antalyaensis, P. antalyaensis myrae, P. antalyaensis anemurius, D—P. isopterus and P. bilgeri." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1441749/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441777>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Overview of the male calling songs of the species of the Poecilimon (P.) inflatus group. A—P. inflatus inflatus,, B—P. inflatus lyciae, C—P. martinae martinae, D—P. cretensis, E—P. antalyaensis antalyaensis, F—P. antalyaensis anemurium, G—P. antalyaensis myrae, H—P. bilgeri, I—P. isopterus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1441777/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441781>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Oscillograms of male calling song (syllable groups only) with stridulatory movement [only in B–D; synchronous registration of left tegmen movement and sound (upper line: upward deflection represents opening, downward closing; lower line: sound)] of P. martinae martinae and P. cretensis. A—P. martinae martinae, B—P. cretensis, single syllable, C—P. cretensis, single echeme, D—P. cretensis, echeme sequence." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1441781/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441789>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Oscillograms of male-female-duets [with female stridulatory movement, only in E; synchronous registration of left tegmen movement and sound (upper line: upward deflection represents opening, downward closing; lower line: sound)] in the P. inflatus group. A—P. inflatus, B—P. martinae martinae, C, D—P. cretensis, E—P. antalyaensis antalyaensis (male song in blue), F—P. bilgeri." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1441789/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441791>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Power spectra of the calling songs of the species and subspecies of the Poecilimon inflatus group." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1441791/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1441793>
    dc:description "FIGURE 22. Relationship of body size and middle peak frequency (given as mean of carrier frequencies at -10 dB below and above peak frequency) in the P. inflatus group. A- Peak frequency versus pronotum length, B- Peak frequency versus length of hind femur. Filled symbols mark data from identified individuals, for open symbols means of sizes were used. The black dots indicate the combinations known from other Poecilimon species (from Heller et al. 2006). X marks P. tschorochensis with huge inflated tegmina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1441793/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

